# Contraponto — core rules

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and existing code in the same package.

## Stack

- Quarkus + Qute + HTMX (no SPA framework). PostgreSQL + Flyway (`db/migration/`).
- Prefer server-rendered HTML fragments over client-side JS.

## Endpoints

- `@ApplicationScoped` + `@Path`. Constructor injection for repositories/services.
- Prefer `Response` for status codes and headers (`X-Toast-Message` via toast helpers).
- Qute: `@CheckedTemplate` inner class; templates co-located as `kebab-case.html` in the same package.

## Data access

- Repositories: `EntityManager` directly, no base class; `Optional` for single results; `@Transactional` on mutating methods.
- Non-trivial domain logic: `@ApplicationScoped` `XxxService` (e.g. `PostPublicationService`, `BlogAudienceService`).
- Side effects across aggregates: CDI events + `@Observes` observers (e.g. `PostPublishedEvent`).

## URLs (do not hardcode in templates)

- Posts: `PostEndpoint.extractUrl(post)` — `/{username}/post/{slug}` or `/{username}/{blogSlug}/post/{slug}`.
- Custom pages: `CustomPagePaths.publicUrl(page)` — always includes `/page/` segment.
- Links in Qute: `TemplateExtensions.url(...)`.

## Auth

- `@Logged` on protected endpoints. Authorization via `LoggedUser`, `BlogAccess`, `UserAccess`, `CustomPageAccess`.
- Roles (`Role` enum): `USER`, `EDITOR`, `USER_ADMINISTRATOR`, `ADMIN` (multi-role via `tb_user_roles`).

## Never

- `System.out.println` — use SLF4J.
- Raw HTML strings for pages — use Qute.
- Modify `CustomPageFilter` without updating `CustomPageCache`; fire `CustomPageChangedEvent` after custom page CUD.

## When adding a feature

ARCHITECTURE.md §9 — entity → repository → service (if needed) → endpoint → template → test → links/navigation.

## When fixing a test

Understand failure first; fix `App` DSL or production code. Do not bypass the DSL with raw WebDriver calls.
